AUDIO: 'Hey, what do you do for a living? &gt;&gt; I manage the IT infrastructure at the local community college. Keeps me busy, but pays the bills. What about you? &gt;&gt; Sounds busy. What do you do for fun? &gt;&gt; When I\'m not untangling network cables.'

[00:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I\'m usually out stargazing. It\'s a good way to unwind, looking at things way bigger than any IT problem. &gt;&gt; Hello and welcome back. In this tutorial, we\'ll set up real-time lip'

[00:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sync and facial animations for metahuman characters enabled by Convey\'s updated Unreal Engine plugin. As your character responds in real time, Convey\'s in-house AI model, Neurosync, processes the audio'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'stream instantly to produce perfectly synchronized lip movements and facial animations. Combined with Metahumans\'s 251 blend shapes, you get incredibly nuanced'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'expressions that adapt dynamically to every word spoken. While convey works with other avatar systems, which we\'ll cover in future tutorials, this video focuses specifically on the Metahuman'

[01:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'setup in Unreal Engine. By the end of this tutorial, you\'ll have a Metahuman that listens and speaks back with accurate lip sync and facial animations. Perfect for creating interactive NPCs, virtual instructors, training'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'simulations, XR applications, and other conversational experiences. Let\'s get into it. We\'re starting with a newly created project using the first person template. Since we\'ve already installed the convey plugin, let\'s enable it. If'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you need help installing the plugin first, check the video linked in the description. To enable the plugin, head over to edit, then plugins, search for convey, and enable it. Now you\'ll have'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to restart the project. Once it opens up, you\'ll be asked again to sign into your Convey account. Once you\'ve signed in and authenticated, you can close this window. To verify that you\'re logged in, simply click on the Convey icon and the'

[01:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dashboard will confirm your status. Now, to get a Metahuman into your project, click on window quicks bridge and go to Metahuman. Select a Metahuman and click to export it to your project. It might'

[02:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'take a few minutes if it\'s the first time you\'ve added a Metahuman to your project. After it\'s complete, look for the Metahumans folder. Double click on the BP file to launch the blueprint. Once it launches, you\'ll be prompted to'

[02:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'enable some missing plugins. Then hit restart. Once it restarts, open up the Metahuman blueprint. What we need to do now is to connect it to the AI. So to do that, we\'ll first add the BP convey'

[02:32] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'chatbot component. This component is responsible for listening to you, generating responses, and more. Under the details panel here, you\'ll need to add a character ID. To get the character'

[02:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ID, first head over to the convey website. Here, you can create a new character or choose one of your existing characters. I\'ll go with one of my existing characters called Alice, who has a very simple backstory. You can also do other'

[02:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'character customizations such as updating speaking style, change the language, voice, and more. For now, let\'s just copy the character ID and paste it within the blueprint. Next, we\'ll need to add the face sync'

[03:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'component, which is responsible for the facial animations. The simplest way to explain the two components would be that the chatbot component is the brain with all the important data and the face sync component is responsible for'

[03:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'interpreting the data and parsing out the correct animation data to run in sync with the audio. Under details, ensure that the lip sync is enabled and that lip-sync mode is set to metahuman blend shapes. Finally, we\'ll need to add the animation component. So for that go'

[03:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to body and under animation class select convey metahuman body anim. Similarly for the face go to animation class and select the convey metahuman face anim.'

[03:49] [scene:talk]
